<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7466&amp;p=32112#p32112"><![CDATA[
If it works only for some directories, go to Control Panel -&gt; Folder Options (called File Explorer Options in Windows 10). Switch to the &quot;View&quot; tab and click &quot;Reset folders&quot;. Now the Folder Options X tweak should work for all folders.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Fri Apr 07, 2017 5:56 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
