<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Classic Explorer: some directories behave differently?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7466&amp;p=32104#p32104"><![CDATA[
Classic Explorer is only a plugin for Windows Explorer that restores *some* functionality. It does not affect the selection of any item in the file pane (right side pane).<br /><br />However, there is a way to do what you are asking for. You can try an app called Folder Options X: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://free-sk.t-com.hr/T800soft/software/FolderOptionsX.html">http://free-sk.t-com.hr/T800soft/softwa ... ionsX.html</a><!-- m --> It should let you toggle the behavior for *all* folders regardless of their names or paths.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Thu Apr 06, 2017 12:23 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
